<content>
    <about>
        <poemTitle xml:id="pulse">Pulse</poemTitle>
        <accArt/>
        <bgInfo>
            <p>Pulse was written for a Creative Writing course in April of 2019, when I was in my
                second year of college.</p>
            <p>The idea of this poem was to communicate that "silence is deafening," the absence of
                a heartbeat growing louder and lourder. A person close to the narrator of the poem
                is dying, and their growing feeling of grief in represented through the symbol of
                sound.</p>
            <p>I used an increasing tempo between stanzas to create a sense of escalation and
                stress, and attempted to simulate a heartbeat by using repetition of the word
                itself.</p>
        </bgInfo>
        <themes>
            <themePoint>Death/Loss</themePoint>
            <themePoint>Grief</themePoint>
            <themePoint>Sound</themePoint>
        </themes>
        <lineInfo>
            <lineInfoPoint passageRef="l12 l11 l12"><q>Empty cavern</q> and <q>cavity</q> refer to
                the ribcage of the person dying.</lineInfoPoint>
            <lineInfoPoint passageRef="l15">The "<q>beeping</q>" is referencing the sound of an EKG
                in a hospital.</lineInfoPoint>
            <lineInfoPoint passageRef="l22 l23">The "<q>long, wooden cage</q>" in this line is a
                casket -- meaning the person dying throughout the beginning of the poem has now
                passed.</lineInfoPoint>
            <lineInfoPoint passageRef="l27">Their tombstone.</lineInfoPoint>
        </lineInfo>
